        conseils: "The Vieux Bassin is Honfleur's heart — stroll along the Sainte-Catherine and Saint-Étienne quays to admire the colourful slate and half-timbered façades. The Church of Sainte-Catherine (free entry) is a marvel of naval carpentry. The Eugène Boudin Museum (€8) holds a fine Impressionist collection. The Jardin des Personnalités (free), by the estuary, pays tribute to Honfleur celebrities (Boudin, Monet, Satie, Baudelaire). For restaurants, try the side streets back from the Vieux Bassin for better value. Erik Satie was born in Honfleur — the Maisons Satie (€6.50) offer a quirky immersive experience.",
        comparaisonTransport: "No train to Honfleur. The Nomad bus (line 20) from Caen via Deauville takes about 2h. The TaxiNeo taxi at €70 — €90 is direct in 50 minutes. For 3-4 passengers (€18-30/person), the only practical and fast option.",
